<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>CAB: 7000 AND 8000 SERIES MODELS - REMOVAL AND INSTALLATION - Door Glass</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x1603814" svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Door Glass</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removal</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>Removal procedures show driver side; passenger side procedures are the same.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Door glass procedures are the same for either front or rear cab doors.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Lower cab door glass to the bottom before removing trim panel.</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove door trim panel. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16038_X1603812.xml" xrefid="x1603812">
                        <emph type="bold">DOOR TRIM PANEL</emph>
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="x1603812"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove door vapor barrier. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16038_X1603813.xml" xrefid="x1603813">
                        <emph type="bold">DOOR VAPOR BARRIER</emph>
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="x1603813"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using a blunt-tip, flat-blade screwdriver, carefully pry regulator arm from the window
                    slide block (
                    <hotlnk document="s16038_33.xml" xrefid="f1603861">Figure 80, Items 3 and 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1603864" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1603864.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 82. Glass Seal and Run Channel</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CAB DOOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. GLASS SEAL AND RUN CHANNEL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Starting at the upper left side, pull glass seal and run channel free from cab door.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove glass seal and run channel.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1603865" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1603865.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 83. Glass Seal and Inner and Outer Belt</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. DOOR GLASS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CAB DOOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. GLASS SEAL AND OUTER BELT</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. GLASS SEAL AND INNER BELT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Modular door hardware assembly purposely not shown in graphic for clarity.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pull glass seal and inner belt free from cab door and remove.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pull glass seal and outer belt free from cab door and remove.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">From outside the cab door, pull door glass upward and remove.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place door glass on a suitable, padded work surface.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Installation</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>Installation procedures show driver side; passenger side procedures are the same.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Door glass procedures are the same for either front or rear cab doors.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Check glass seal, run channels, and inner and outer belts for damage. Replace if
                                needed.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">From outside the cab door, install the door glass and position into the left and right
                    run channels. Ensure the door glass is in the run channels and moves freely before proceeding (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603864">Figure 82</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lower the door glass to the bottom.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the glass seal and inner belt and press down firmly into cab door (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603865">Figure 83, Items 2 and 4</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the glass seal and outer belt and press down firmly into cab door (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603865">Figure 83, Items 2 and 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Starting at the upper right, begin pressing glass seal and run channel into the cab door
                    . Proceed until entire glass seal and run channel is firmly seated into cab door (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603864">Figure 82</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach the regulator arm to the window slide block (
                    <hotlnk document="s16038_33.xml" xrefid="f1603861">Figure 80, Items 3 and 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>For manual windows, temporarily attach regulator handle to operate. For electric windows,
                        temporarily connect electrical connector to operate. Remove regulator handle or disconnect
                        electrical connector when next step is complete.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Raise and lower window to ensure free movement. If binding occurs, find, locate, and
                    correct problem before continuing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install door vapor barrier. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16038_X1603813.xml" xrefid="x1603813">
                        <emph type="bold">DOOR VAPOR BARRIER</emph>
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="x1603813"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install door trim panel. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16038_X1603812.xml" xrefid="x1603812">
                        <emph type="bold">DOOR TRIM PANEL</emph>
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="x1603812"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
